 in early access. Once again, I am very much aware that Dead State is still in beta and that it's in early access but this feels more like an alpha. For a game that has been in development for so long there is not much to it and I'm pretty disappointed about that. I'm disappointed that after release date delay after relase date delay this is all we got. This is just my opinion however and everyone is entitled to their own opinions. I know there will be some who agree with me and many who will disagree and that's okay.September 21st: Started playing again to check out the new update. Gameplay stopped after 7 days that said ""Thanks for playing!"" as dialog with survivors went on over the screen. After the dialog I pressed ""Continue"" and was taken to the main menu. I'm not sure why that happened other then something happened where the game thinks it's the first seven days demo.November 3rd: I wanted to try the new update and see how things came along since I last played. I saved the game during the intro sequence right after I created my character. I loaded the game (or tried to) but was met with an error ""CGC::GetPC - could not find playable character."" I have no idea why this is occuring."
