76561198118097343,Recommended,239840,14197515,"Posted: 27 January, 2015",all,booster654,"I loved this despite its flaws. No bells and whistles and felt like an old 8 bit adventure where the atmosphere came from the writing plus you had to use your imagination instead of relying bombastic gfx. The writing and dialogue is where this stands out. All of the characters are individuals and prompt a range of emotions. Some are hilarious and some down right infuriating.The turn based combat is simple but varied enough to work out elaborate attacks especially when you start to obtain decent weapons and armor.The managment and building side to the game are great and really add to the involvement.I've read a lot about its bugs but all I encountered were some side missions not ticked off the board.All in all its simply a great adventure which, for me, smacked of the right kind of nostalgia. It reminds me of what made GTA Vice City so great. No single aspect stood out, except the writing in the this case, but everything came together to make a thoroghly enjoyable and remorable experience. 10/10 for me.Oh, and the endings. Well I loved both of them. This is the most memorable game I've played in a long long time."
