76561198118623945,Recommended,239840,33275064,Posted: 5 July,all,Gottkönig,"Great game! One of those, that after you're bored of gaming in general, can still enjoy - which is rare from my perspective.Pros:- It's complex and it's unforgiving which is fun and challenging. The social- and base-building-related game mechanics are well performed.- The characters in the game (which it is full of) are interesting and mostly well written. They make sense when they talk to you. They are not randomized sandbox NPCs which give you quests and hail at you for completing them but the game actually spends a lot of focus on real social interaction between a good diversity of characters. There's a good soul, a preacher, people with challenging mentals stats .... even racists, rapists and murderers. And you somehow need to manage to get those people to work together. I liked that!- Going out to look for much needed ressources for the rest of the team is fun aswell. The levels to play through are basically non-generic but handmade and not too repetetive. I was surprised a lot by a variety of ideas the developers came up with in order to surprise me. The map is basically open world with a few exceptions, enabling you to make your own decissions on what would be best for your people and letting the game appear less linear which it otherwise would be.- Combat AI is okay. Not a masterpiece but totally okay.- Lot's of well written flavor texts - if you're into that.- Huge variety of items you can possibly find while scavenging.- A smart yet mostly subtile humour throughout the entire game which made me smile a lot.- Very cheap game for the time I played and felt entertained by it.- Developers had a good eye for details in general. I think you can feel that they made this game because they wanted to make a great game and not because they wanted to make the cash flow. That's probably even the biggest plus I give this game. You hardly ever see something like this from the big studios and the big titles.Cons:- To get right to the point: After the first half of the game when you scavenged enough food and supplies for the other half of the game, killed the bad guys with the best weapons which you looted and now use for yourself, the game stops being challenging and interesting. The lack of lategame content is in my opinion the biggest flaw. When no enemy gives you a tough fight anymore, you have enough food for months to come and everyone in your shelter is completely happy, the game pretty much loses it's point and becomes a ""The Sims"" clone with dead rats, some social intrigues and a whole lot of mayonnaise. All that isn't too bad becase noone forces you to actually leave the shelter and go out to look for things you allready have more than enough of but staying at home and looking at a wall is the only other option you have then.- Combat balancing is a bit off even in the first half of the game. But as mentioned above: Once you have good weapons and armor, the game lacks challenge. Have someone with the best armor and a medkit standing in front taking hardly any damage but your opponents and bring some people with big guns to kill your foes from a distance. Master that and you'll master the game. Other or similar tactics might generally work aswell. Too easy!- Bugs and crashes. Game crashes around every 10 hours on average on my system which arguably is still okay, but gave me a headtache for a few moments. Similar to bugs where I want to say that the game isn't too buggy, really, but at some points in the game really problematic. For example: Being stuck in a door after appearing in a level and bad guys immediatly shooting at you while you're stuck, unable to free yourself, unable to get to that area from another entry area, only able to fire back from inside that door and hope you win because that's the only way to unstuck yourself. Also: Enemies in similar situations. Door bugs. They are a problem.- Graphics are a bit clumsy. I personally didn't feel bad about it but thought I should mention it.- Game gave me nightmares about having to eat tons of mayonnaise in a potential zombie apocalypse. I'm dead serious about it. Dead State serious.There's no game without flaws in it on the market. Even the classic Windows Minesweeper has a few. If I break it down to my core opinion with Dead State: Reanimated, it is a good game. Mostly in the first half of playing it but then again: it's a long game! Other games I enjoyed a lot took around 7 hours maybe 20. Dead States first half is about 30 hours. Getting my point?I cleary recommend buying this if you're into the genre.Thanks to the developers for making this game, I can only imagine how much time and effort you must have spent on it and you have my respect for your work."
