76561197961249924,Recommended,239840,18192962,"Posted: 25 September, 2015",all,[ __ ] Teaks,"Surprisingly good!  I wouldn't give $30, but would value it at $15-$20 easily (grab during a sale).I've loved turn-based squad strat games since JA2.  I'd still rank that as the top; give 2nd place to Silent Storm (up until they bring in the unicorn suits of rainbow bright), and give this one 3rd place.  Just finished my first full playthrough:PRO's: Solidly done turn-based squad strat game.  It's got a base with lots of upgrades, tons of loot, decent selection of weapons, limited resources (ammo, grenades, fuel, etc), good character progression, zombie killing fun, base management, character interactions are fun, etc.  Basically it's got a LOT of stuff done RIGHT.CON's:   Not as many different weapons or upgrades as I'd like (thinking JA2 again); approx 3-6 per ammo type (7 ammo types; maybe 20-25 weapons total).  The side stories are limited in content and usually amount to: bring character A to place B from their past; get special dialog, end of quest.  Not bad, but could have been made into much more.  There are a few bugs; I had about 8 crashes total over my playthrough, but with ample auto-saves you never lose more than the last 10-20 minutes.  Last and biggest complaint is the simplistic AI.  Dont expect you're enemies to Mcguyver up an ultralight and surprise you with an L-shaped.  It's just not there, still: what do you expect from zombies?Still a postive experience; really recommend this one if you're a fan of the genre."
