,Recommended,239840,18536855,"Posted: 17 October, 2015",all,Doeetright,"Looters and Zombies Oh My!  Think Project Zomboid with a Tactical Battle System!Dead State: Reanimated is all about survival, you start off with a small group of people in a shelter and you can choose how you want to expand, when you want to expand, or who you want to expend.  The game comes with some critical choices that you might need to actually read a guide about if you're working on achievements.  Overall the game deserves at least a 7.5/10 from me and I recommend picking it up, below are some of the key reasons why or why not to!Pros:Rather Unique (in what I've played) noise system in which you fire a gun or shoot off a firecracker and things hear it and go to the location.  Makes for more strategic gameplay, can't always be a firefight, sometimes you want to make noise to attract zombies to enemy locations.  Rather cool system.HUGE fan of Tactical Battle systems that are similar Final Fantasy Tactics and Fire Emblem games, mix in just enough looting, inventory management and rpg elements and you have yourself a solid game.If you're a fan of the Zombie Genre, or being able to Control what happens to your ""followers"", like say take them to a random location and stab them to death.  Then this is the game for you.Cons:Bugs - In multiple playthroughs I ended up with a character laying flat on his face in the infirmary.  Not sure what this was about.  There was also an endless encounter between Zombies and Enemy NPCs where I did nothing but press spacebar for a few hours and they fought the whole time (eventually I had to restart the encounter).  Mind you, this game is an indie dev and I'm all about supporting smaller companies, so I assume that these bugs will be fixed at a later date even though that later date may be a while away.Price - This is kind of a big one believe it or not, I got the game when it was a bit cheaper so it doesn't affect me as much.  When there are awesome games like Shadowrun out there and many others in this tactical genre at the 15$ price point it makes me question why this game is double the price.  I could understand 20$, I just think anything more than that for this game is a little much.  It's a good game, sure the dev spent a lot of time on it and all.  I'll wait for Dead State's sister game Age of Decadence to be Bundled or go on sale below the 20$ price point before I purchase it."
