76561198010046642,Recommended,239840,13317131,"Posted: 11 December, 2014",all,Vermithrax,"I am not normally the type to write reviews, but I feel that Dead State is worth a break from the ordinary.I have been playing since early access (First Seven Days release) and gone back for multiple playthroughs with each patch release right up until full release.End result, over 300 hours played on this game and I dont feel I have wasted any of them.YES, there are bugs, some of them are immersion breaking, some are annoying, but nothing OVERLY game breaking. The Devs are incredibly quick to respond to any new bugs found and are continually consulting the player base to find and eliminate bugs as they happen. To me, this is incredibly satisfying as I know my opinion as a consumer is valued.As to the game itself?If you are looking for a pulse-pounding thrill ride as you slaughter increasingly tough and varied monsters in graphic ways with an assortment of zany and idiosincratic weapons....Look somewhere else.Dead State is a htoughtful game that encourages you to plan ahead, from catering to the needs and wants of your fellow survivors to deciding when, where and how you and your team will fight.Sometimes it is better to sneak through an area, get what you can and get out quietly.I found I was investing into the fellow survivors, thinking outside the game to better understand thier motives and how best to make them work. A sure sign of good writing (Although you may not believe it simply from appearances)Finally, if like me, you have played more than your fair share of RPG's (especially from the 90's and 00's) the isometric viewpoint, the turn based combat and even the JRPGesque base and NPC collection will tickle all the nostalgia bones and keep you coming back for more.tl:dr?A great game that may still seem a little rough around the edges, but a must have for any RPG and/or Zombie Survival fan"
