,Recommended,239840,33557550,Posted: 15 July,all,Bobby,"LOVE IT !   Played around 30+ hours so far and its everything i ever wanted in a zombie survival game.  The story is great, i love the aspect of building shelter upgrades, assigning building jobs, finding new allies, and the fact that whilst the main story seems the same no matter how many times you play it through - there are always nice little random events that make it seem like a brand new game each time.If i am being picky, a couple of things id like to see added/improve (i know probably unlikely as game is a few years old but..) :1) Looting system - either give more looting events or less (i'll explain that).   If you find a car or van, you cant loot it because the game has nothing to give you from it, so then why are they so many ""lootable things"" like zombies that allow you to click on them but nothing inside.  It shouldnt be that hard to code that an object can only be looted/clicked if it has something to actually loot.2) Parts seem really hard to find yet there is an abundance of ""uncollectable / visual only"" items in each area, i get it must be balanced but again i cant help but cheer every time i find parts as they seem so rare, yes i did build recycling but its the finding of parts im talking about.3) Space allocation - would be nice to have an extra plot of land and you decide what its used for: farm / shooting range / recreation, etc rather than having set plots that then cant be expanded, example lets say you want a farm but you want a huge farm using all available land, not just a little greenhouse on the roof. But you would have to make the choice - if you build a farm you then cant have anything else on that land.  Maybe even the option to expand the perimeter.4) travelling at night time - i get that the game wants you back in your shelter by 8pm but why cant you say spend the night in an abandoned house then set off again in morning back to the shelter?  If it were real life thats what you would do.  Even if it were just a clickable button on the map next to the house you were at that said ""stay the night"" and gave you a percentage survival chance of you not being attacked during the night would be good. Then you could pick and choose the best option to spend the night and head back to the shelter the next day.5) romance options - even if it were just an occasional conversation or two that could lead to an ally getting a bonus towards agreeing with you would be nice.6) combat movement - the square chess like system can be very annoying especially if you have an injured ally that then cant escape because all spaces are blocked, really there shoukld be allowances for this like maybe when they panic they can run through taken spaces or that moving through a taken space as an additonal movement point/points penalty.Dont let my above 6 things put you off, its a great game and already has been worth every penny i paid for it.  Buy it !"
