76561198116179964,Recommended,239840,34664304,Posted: 1 September,all,tbassett,"So, I recently revisited this game and have found it to be quite interesting. It has an expansive storyline that branches well based on character skill and choices.  Items are interesting and balanced enough to actually make you sit and ponder which item to use.  There are a ton of custom tile sets in this game. The morale system is unique and works really well in comparison to other games.  This game is definitely one that other game developers should look at as something of a milestone in survival gameplay.The original reason I didn't recommend the game is because the UI is a mess.  It is extremely difficult to figure out what you're supposed to do in the home base and in combat, the hex overlay doesn't properly represent the actual movement (although the tooltip does).  Someone clearly put a lot of hard work into the game because it is seriously contented out, but some easy fixes to the UI, in-game help, and tool tips would have made this game wildly popular.  Hopefully either the developers will pick it back up and fix it or allow someone else to come in and do some fixes. If you're interested in the game, be prepared for a steep learning curve, some pointless base micro running between objects, and lack of polish that comes with a game that has been abandoned by its developers.  For fans of the survival genre, it is a study in both what to do and what not to do to make a good survival game.Original Review:This game has a great concept and was mostly fleshed out, but was never completely finished before launch. There is no ongoing support from the developers and probably would have be great had they finished with another 3 months of work. Unfortunately, it's buggy and incomplete and I can't recommend this game to a friend."
