76561198021662957,Recommended,239840,13278393,"Posted: 7 December, 2014",all,xXI Mr Two IXx,"Dead State stands alone as a Zombie TBS Rpg, mostly because there aren't any others. The game's core is great, the concept is spot on, and Turned based strategy is, in my opinion, the best mechanical base for a zombie game. The final product isn't as good as I hoped it would be when I first read about it two years ago. But I still think the released game is enjoyable, if short of the potential the setting and style could have provided.IssuesDead State uses the Torque engine just like Age of Decadence, its not that pretty. Better than 2d pixels but it also lacks the ""retro charm"" some pixel games capture.There is very little scripted content like what is found in Age of Decadence, I enjoyed that content in AOD and wish some of these engine utilizations made it into Dead State.Its psuedo open world, you really have no choice in where you go or stay only in the order of actions. This is the biggest issue I have with game. There is very little emergent content, and NPC interactions are very limited. Its either friendly will join you, or shoot first ask questions later. If you shoot first you make everyone sad though.UI is clunky and this is a title you should read the manual for, otherwise you will be complaining about follower item management in the forums.The goodIts a zombie tbs RPG!Classic zombies, ie walking dead style. No sci-fi exploding, mutuant jumping zombies. Could use more of them on screen at once IMO.All the classic themes are present. Gather supplies, fix up your shelter, defend against zombies and bandits, or be a bandit.Good selection of weapons, items, skills, upgrades, etc. You can build a self sustaining fortress, but you can't leave and live in a house of your choosing.This is a great base and I'm excited to see what/when mods get ahold of it."
