be impossible anyway). Or only one zomb per square is affected from a grenade. More zombs per square also making aiming at them to matter of patience and constant clicking.Fighting is also buggy. When having enemies in fighting range even though you have attacked them already the game sometimes decides to end the fighting mode. End all effects (from fire grenades or buffs or so) letting become enemies aggro and giving them also 2 extra turns ... just to screw you and your tactics over.That and even more bugs ... there are so many that I start to forget some of them.And there are those questionable game play decisions. Some of them feel like remains of a whole more complex system which was scrapped last minute.There are a few of them that annoy me:First of all why is this game in FU*KING imperial? Never learned proper units in school?Then there is e.g. the 200 pound limit of the trunk ... ok that much would make sense for horses ... but for a car? ... where is it from? Some east-European communist country ... build in the 80th ... and held together only by duckt-tape?Also some of those object weights making no sense at all... I bet the developer at some point said: ""Screw it, deadline is rushing in, we are rolling dice"".Map can't be viewed unless you are scavenger team.POI on map can't be marked for further planning.Map filled up already but planned to come back later to one point since it is still full of goodies ... but something more important is to be done before? ... Fat chance .. or more like no chance ... especially if you have to put the game away for some time ... you probably won't remember.No F*CKING sorting for the inventories. (aside from categories, which aren't even working fully, or even available [see trunk]) If the shelter storage fills up looking for something becomes a nightmare.Not sure if bad game play decision or a bug: Some medical equipment isn't showing up in the Medical tab.To name them:All drugs: as ...FlashbackSoothinumAdrenaline ShotStuporaxI might have forgotten someor Medical SatchelThe game does not often communicate clearly ... some decisions are pure guesswork.For dialogs you might argue that in RL you would also not have those hints I am asking for, but I say you would have others like facial expression and the way people talk ... e.g. you can say the same sentence but the way you say it can make your opponent know that it  meant serious, or as joke, or you annoyed as ****.And in RL you would have a lot more interaction and therefore know those ppl a whole lot better.Game also failed to tell me if I need to equip every NPC in my group or if I just can trash the stuff.Also after building the correlated rooms. Do I still the the parts? In meanwhile I also got my hands on spare parts of those ... Do they do something? (e.g. 5 dumbbells)Tasks... duration as well as requirements seem complete arbitrary .. you also can't look what a character could do without interrupting his work. Only way to make this save is at 8:00 AM.Warning that a bonus is not given is showing up when reassigning tasks at 8:00 AM ... when it shouldn't.I understand how the noise system works in this game, but calling it dB is driving me nuts.PLEASE DEVELOPER: If you have not clue at least take a short look into wikipedia. The dB unit has a logarithmic scale. Means 20 dB is not twice but ten times as loud as 10 dB, and 30 dB is hundred times as loud.Doubtful decision to make people run around the whole time ... probably to make it more ""lively"".IF YOU WANT FU*KING TALK TO ONE PERSON ... WHICH IS NOT EVEN POSSIBLE FROM THE GOALS SCREEN .... YOU HAVE TO RUN AROUND FOR HOURS TILL YOU FINALLY FIND THEM.If I could I would knife everyone and put them into the infirmary ... just because then I know where they are."
