,Recommended,239840,16921115,"Posted: 6 July, 2015",all,Kuman,"First off, i want to respond to someone that clearly hasn't played the game long enough to know the basic combat mechanics, so people won't avoid this game based on a rather misinformed review:""-can't tank them""You can. Maximize vigor, strength, and put on a heavy armor....But that still doesn't mean you should, since dead character will stay dead. Avoid any direct confrontation if possible, whether it's against looters or zombies.""-can't kite them""Every type of enemy has a certain vision range. Just make your party hides in a certain spot and *very* carefully send one party member to kite one or two of the zombies.""-can't evade them""Put more points towards agility. But this is a survival strategy game in the first place, so what you really want to do is to kill off any threats as carefully and quietly as possible.And to add: positioning is *crucial* in any strategy game, so if you somehow messed up and got a party member surrounded by zombies, then you're the only one to blame for that.""-can't sneak past them""Stealth is a totally viable option, and is the preferred way of doing things in this game. Zombies has a rather small(er) visibility cone, so you CAN evade them and quite easily too compared to sneaking past looters.They do have better sense of hearing though, so if you're planning to do a sneak attack do it quickly. Initiate the attack a few squares away from behind the zombie.""-must rely on luck to beat them""Every strategy game that has RNG relies on both skill and luck. I see no problem with this.""-if you don't outnumber them 2 or 3 to 1, it has a high probability of a loss.""Outnumbering them does indeed kills them more effectively, but that doesn't mean you can't send a party member with high Vigor and Strength/Agility plus a high enough melee skill to face off against a zombie one-on-one.I'm not saying the game is perfect. It's buggy at times, writing is... okay, and the graphics and animations are not exactly what you'd call stellar...But the game still offers exploration in a rather big world map, the strategy part is quite solid, you can recruit and manage survivors who also gives you choices and consequences that matters, and the best aspect i personally love the most: homebase management. I just wish they would offer more base other than the school though, and more interations between each survivors.Overall it's at least a 7/10 game, and is totally worth the price tag."
