76561198031397287,Recommended,239840,26868246,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,haijikai2,"There is always been a love for the classic style that indeed is the original X-Com.  Developing a squad, a team, and gradually through smart play and fighting exploring different areas and using the terrain both for and against.Dead State finds a way to combine the style of that classic game into another popular genre, the zombie apocolypse.  And it really is a brilliant game!  Not only do you have to deal with the different Survivors you can rescue, but you have to deal with their demands and your own.  Plus there's a lot of wonderful ""self character' development, in that you can choose so many little details for your own character.And there's a wealth of ""background material"" inside the game itself that can draw you into ths world and it's history.  And the choices you make throughout the game are remembered, both the good, and the bad.  You set the course.Classic turn style with squad based tactics, just remember the living can be more dangerous."
