76561198197302835,Recommended,239840,33254536,Posted: 4 July,all,fitey384,"The details in the areas are outstanding and the game itself is enthralling and entertaining. I greatly enjoy the game and, while I do believe it may have a niche audience in that not everyone likes tactical rpgs or zombie games or maintaining resources and such, it is a phenomenal entry for anyone who likes anything similar to it. I was hesitant to purchase it and waited for the steam summer sale to buy it and I have to say it would be worth the full price.If I have to scrounge for negatives, it might be the cliche storyline (particularly from apocolypse games) but that hardly matters for the type of game unless you're the type of person who really wants an intriguing storyline. That is not to say that the game itself is not intriguing. Every map seems to have a story of its own with spray paint on walls, bloody scenes, etc. Every map has something of interest. One map I explored was a surprisingly immaculate house in the woods with no zombies but attack dogs and a dead man out back. After picking the lock of his shack out back, I discovered a torture room and found my favorite blade in the chest there alongside several other weapons. Additionally, just behind the shack was a shovel and fresh graves hinting at a terrible history even before the apocalypse. It is small things like that that make you feel invested in this world and the game itself.Only one more potential negative is the lack of relationships within the game. Sure, you can inspire people and even get them on your side but there is no friendships or exploring a person's identity further than a few conversations and perhaps a request or two. If the people suddenly become unhappy, from lack of food or whatever, they will leave or try to take over despite all the things you go through together. This minor complaint could simply be from my love of deep characters. It would not have to be a romantic relationship or anything, just something to make me feel more invested in the survival of the individuals within the game. Despite this, I did feel more involved with these characters than I did with characters from other games, even AAA games. Again, I'm probably just being picky because what is in the game is amazing regardless of my wishes."
,Recommended,239840,33444748,Posted: 10 July,all,kinghavoc,"All the adventure and excitement of the great turn based console era rpg's with well thought out character interaction and a level of forthought fit for any strategy gamer, this game will pull you into the world and have you strive to lead your group through the apocolyptic days in rural Texas. Be Forewarned read the manual to get the control and interface, and read/watch others commentary on the elements of gameplay to expect.Once your ready jump in and keep at it, it will take several hours, days, likely weeks of play sessions. I have approached the midgame point a couple of times and restarted seeing opportunities to try things new ways.The base management is simple enough, the dialog tree is deceptively simple looking but after you see small changes showing up you realize how uniquely well crafted it is. There are some scripted events along the way but there are many interaction that flavor or outright change others later on. This character/Ally-NPC interaction dynamic is what gives this game replayability. You will ask yourself what if I have this person try this job, say this instead of say that, or build something sooner rather than later. Even though much of the experience is predictable the possibilities are very distinct and impact your game. Overall this game shines for me as it was truely well crafted. Of course there are downsides, for one the intro tutorial is too dry and not good at showing you certain things you need to know, adding some pictures to the pop up hints would go a long way for this, further and in game encyclopedia akin to what Civilization has would be just as good if not better. This game feels like playing X-Com with survival/zombies replacing the fighting of aliens.I got this game on sale but it was easliy worth more than many others I tried on that same sale. Knowing what I know now  I would save money and just buy this and dump a few other titles that I may have less flattering things to say about."
